How Node.js Works
V8 JS Engine (C++)
* interprets JS -> binary

Non-Blocking
* does not wait for I/O ops
  - file ops
  - db calls
  - network calls
* events & callbacks used to synchronize I/O ops with
  "actors"

Single-Threaded
* uses event loop to perform non-blocking ops
* I/O operation -> 
  event loop continues -> 
  I/O operation returns -> 
  triggers callback -> 
  call back goes to event queue -> 
  event loop picks up callback

Common Node.js Uses
APIs
CLI tools
Real-time apps
Microservices
Web servers
Web scraping

NB: Node is NOT GOOD for CPU-intensive tasks


